IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: DEVELOPMENTAL SERVICES CENTER (DSC) SUPPORTS PEOPLE WITH DISABILITIES IN LIVING A RICH AND MEANINGFUL LIFE. SUPPORTS INCLUDE EMPLOYMENT, COMMUNITY DAY SERVICES, RESIDENTIAL, CASE MANAGEMENT AND EARLY INTERVENTION. DSC PROVIDES SERVICES TO APPROXIMATELY 1,200 INDIVIDUALS PER YEAR.
IRS990.MissionDesc: DEVELOPMENTAL SERVICES CENTER (DSC) SUPPORTS PEOPLE WITH DISABILITIES IN LIVING A RICH AND MEANINGFUL LIFE.
IRS990.Desc: RESIDENTIAL SERVICES PROVIDES COMMUNITY-BASED RESIDENTIAL HOUSING ALTERNATIVES SUCH AS GROUP HOMES, A SEMI-SUPPORTED APARTMENT BUILDING, AND PRIVATE HOMES AND APARTMENTS. PEOPLE RECEIVE ONE-ON-ONE SUPPORT IN LIFE AREAS THAT ARE MEANINGFUL TO THEM. THE PROGRAM PROVIDES FOR HEALTH, SAFETY AND CHOICE, ALL OF WHICH ARE PRIORITIES TO ENJOY AN INDEPENDENT LIFE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: EMPLOYMENT SERVICES PROVIDES ASSESSMENT, TRAINING, EMPLOYMENT, AND EMPLOYMENT SUPPORT. THIS INCLUDES ASSISTANCE SEEKING AND MAINTAINING EMPLOYMENT, ON-THE-JOB TRAINING, AND ONGOING SKILL BUILDING. SUPPORT HELPS TO INCREASE INDEPENDENCE, QUALITY OF LIFE AND ECONOMIC SELF-SUFFICIENCY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: COMMUNITY DAY SERVICES ASSISTS INDIVIDUALS IN ACHIEVING GREATER LEVELS OF INDEPENDENCE AND SELF-SUFFICIENCY. SERVICES INCLUDE SKILL DEVELOPMENT IN AREAS SUCH AS COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT, COMMUNICATION, RECREATION, LEISURE, EMPLOYMENT AND VOLUNTEER OPPORTUNITIES. INDIVIDUALIZED SUPPORTS ARE PROVIDED TO ENHANCE QUALITY OF LIFE AND INDEPENDENCE.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: CASE MANAGEMENT AND FAMILY SUPPORT WORKS TO ENSURE THAT INDIVIDUALS' NEEDS ARE IDENTIFIED, ASSESSED, PLANNED FOR, AND MONITORED THROUGH A PERSON-CENTERED APPROACH. SERVICE LINKAGE FOR COMMUNITY RESOURCES IS A PRIORITY.

FAMILY DEVELOPMENT CENTER - AN EARLY INTERVENTION PROGRAM THAT OFFERS ASSISTANCE TO FAMILIES OF INFANTS AND TODDLERS WHO ARE EXPERIENCING OR ARE AT RISK FOR DELAYS IN DEVELOPMENT, OR HAVE IDENTIFIED SPECIAL NEEDS.
OTHER PROGRAM EXPENSES PROVIDE PROGRAMS AND SERVICES TO INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES IN OUR COMMUNITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS ANNUALLY COMPLETE CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS AND THE ORGANIZATION REVIEWS NEW VENDORS FOR ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO HAS AN AUDIT COMMITTEE THAT IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CEO COMPENSATION: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE PROVIDES AN ANNUAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION FOR THE CEO. THE PROCESS INCLUDES SOLICITING INPUT FROM THE ENTIRE BOARD AND THE CHAIR OF DISABLED CITIZENS FOUNDATION (RELATED PARTY) AND UTILIZING SALARY COMPARABILITY DATA FROM INDEPENDENT SOURCES AT OTHER NONPROFITS COMPARABLE TO DSC. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE PROVIDES A WRITTEN PERFORMANCE APPRAISAL TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL AND THE DSC BOARD GIVES FINAL APPROVAL TO ALL POLICIES AND PROCEDURES ASSOCIATED WITH THE CEO'S EVALUATION AND COMPENSATION. OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES: THE DIRECTOR OF HUMAN RESOURCES OBTAINS A COMPARABILITY STUDY ANNUALLY THAT IS USED FOR REVIEW OF SALARY RANGES FOR DSC EMPLOYEES.
